# Close Order Feature & TP Clarification

Add the ability for users to close an active trade manually and record the final P/L, while emphasizing that the Take Profit (TP) value entered at the start was an expected target.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> I will implement a "Chốt lệnh" (Close Order) button that appears only for running trades. When clicked, it will ask for the final P/L % and any updated psychology/mistake notes.

## Proposed Changes

### [Core Logic]

#### [MODIFY] [script.js](file:///home/digimed/.gemini/antigravity/script.js)
- Add `closeTrade(id)` function.
- Update `renderTradeToRecent` and `renderTradeToFull` to include a "Chốt" button for trades with `pl === null`.
- Update the UI to label TP as "TP (Dự kiến)" to match the user's request.

#### [MODIFY] [styles.css](file:///home/digimed/.gemini/antigravity/styles.css)
- Add styles for the "Chốt lệnh" button (e.g., a subtle border or a specific accent color).

### [UI Elements]

